detected_clauses.detection_method: Identified roles of Landlord and Tenant in the rental agreement
detected_clauses.supporting_text: Landlord, as the Landlord, rents to Tenant, as the Tenant, the Premises referred to as [Premises Description], which is part of the Project known as [Project Name].
detected_clauses.summary: Identified parties involved in the lease and the description of the premises.

detected_clauses.detection_method: Found keywords indicating rental agreement duration
detected_clauses.supporting_text: The rental agreement will commence [Start Date], and continue on a month-to-month basis. Either party, on 30-days’ written notice, may terminate this rental agreement.
detected_clauses.summary: Rental agreement starts on [Start Date] and is month-to-month with a 30-day termination notice.

detected_clauses.detection_method: Identified terms related to possession delivery and tenant rights
detected_clauses.supporting_text: Possession to be delivered to Tenant on commencement of the rental agreement, or on [Possession Date]. If Landlord is unable to recover and deliver possession... Tenant may terminate the rental agreement if Landlord does not deliver possession within 10 days.
detected_clauses.summary: Possession is to be delivered on [Possession Date], with specific rights if possession is delayed.

detected_clauses.detection_method: Identified currency amounts and payment terms
detected_clauses.supporting_text: Tenant to pay, in advance, $5,000 monthly rent on the first day of each month... Tenant to pay a charge of $[AMOUNT]... interest will accrue from the due date on the amount at 18% per annum until paid.
detected_clauses.summary: Monthly rent of $5,000 due on the 1st with a 5-day grace period and late fees applicable.

detected_clauses.supporting_text: Tenant will obtain and maintain commercial general liability... Tenant will obtain and maintain a standard fire insurance policy with extended coverage for theft and vandalism to the extent of 100% of the replacement value.
detected_clauses.summary: Tenant must maintain liability insurance of at least [AMOUNT] and fire insurance covering 100% of replacement value.

detected_clauses.detection_method: Identified terms regarding Landlord's right to enter
detected_clauses.supporting_text: Tenant agrees to make the Premises available on 24 hours' notice for entry by Landlord for necessary repairs, alterations, or inspections.
detected_clauses.summary: Landlord may enter the premises with 24 hours' notice for necessary reasons.

detected_clauses.detection_method: Identified provisions related to Tenant's breach
detected_clauses.supporting_text: If Tenant breaches any provision of this rental agreement, Landlord may exercise its rights, including the right to collect future rental losses after forfeiture of possession.
detected_clauses.summary: Landlord has rights to collect future rental losses if Tenant breaches the agreement.
